  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Able to plan, implement and monitor work schedule for all necessary sites</li><li>Ability to source for suppliers / sub-cons for smooth operation on site</li><li>Independent & able to resolve any technical difficulties & problem may arise on site</li><li>Ensure operation are carried out timely, smoothly and safely for handling over to clients</li><li>Prepare & responsible for all necessary site safety procedures and documentation to authorize</li><li>Correspondence & Liaising with clients' representatives, authorities department, Main-contractors, Sub-con, suppliers & in house workers</li><li>Prepare site program chart for management review regularly</li><li>Attend show round / site meetings as & when require</li><li>Other related duties assign by company from time to time</li><li>Conduct setting out and mark level on site</li><li>Work closely with workers, subcontractors</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least a Diploma/Degree with 2 - 3 years relevant experience in Building construction</li><li>Possess good communication skill for effective follow-up and attention to details</li><li>Preferred to be able to speak in Mandarin (Optional)</li><li>Ability to interact with all levels in a professional & responsive manner</li><li>Display maturity and able to handle stress</li><li>Willingness to learn and progress</li><li>Enthusiastic team player</li></ul>",
